			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				( ... You know, it actually made me laugh hysterically until I fell out of my chair when I read some of these vaguely insulting comments about my post. <BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Listen, '' pal.'' I knew about the blasted events on all the other servers. I knew about the events in the other zones. I attended them all. I received a wonderful necklace, a nice, albeit ugly, robe, and a great bracer. I grabbed the Tome, and the Cloak. I helped an SK buddy grab three pieces of armor, and that -useless- Harbinger. <BR>
<BR>
Please, don't think that I'm on a high horse, but I've decided to nip these budding flames in the.. err.. bud.<BR>
<BR>
I -knew- about every event. I -know- about every item. I destroyed a few of the items that I received after picking them up and comparing stats with items that I already had available. I typed this because I thought it'd be nice to treat people to a change of pace, besides the boring, droning, quasi-informative dissertations and item lists that most others have been posting.<BR>
<BR>
I also did it from a roleplaying perspective, because.. well.. I do quite a bit of roleplaying. <BR>
<BR>
I find it hard to believe that there are -so- many idiots in the world. Truly. People who read posts like this that took more than three minutes to write.. Posts that were virtually devoid of any grammatical errors, and even somewhat entertaining.. People who actually -read- these things, and then purposefully -find- something to whine about.<BR>
<BR>
You couldn't do a better job of writing it. If you can, come up here and prove me wrong. I didn't post this thing for me. I did it for you. Bite my head off, see if I care. <BR>
<BR>
:: yawn :: As for those who actually gave me heartfelt compliments.. thank you. You guys are the people that make life worth living, and EQ worth playing. If people like you didn't exist, I'd have to go around murdering everyone. <BR>
<BR>
Let's face it. That'd really suck.<BR>
<BR>
So, keep being nice. You're doing the public a service.<BR>
<BR>
... and, flamers? Keep ticking me off. I work much more efficiently when properly motivated. <BR>
<BR>
;)<BR>
<BR>
Ciao. )<BR>
<BR>
- Demetrii Spiritdrinker<BR>
- Sentinels of Justice<BR>
&quot; ... You know, I can't possibly fathom why the banker tolerates my animating corpses in the middle of the lobby, before wishing me good day, and thanking me for visiting ... while the merchants would sooner spit on me than accept my coins ... You could say, ' Demetrii, that's just the way the world works, sometimes. '<BR>
<BR>
Yes, you -could- say that. <BR>
<BR>
Until you noticed just how naive you sounded. &quot;
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
