	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I've heard a lot of people complaining about high lvl players kill stealing their mobs during this event.  I have felt this frustration as well.  But it occured to me (lvl 26 sk on Torv) that the ks'ing going on was mostly not intentional.  The increadible lag in the zones caused both sides of most disputes to think they were to ones getting ks'ed.  There were numerous times where I saw a mob all by itself, I attack it, and about 15 seconds later my screen finally shows me the group that was already there.  Now once i noticed, I gave them the benifit of the doubt and assumed they had been fighting it before i got there and i backed off.<BR>
<BR>
My point is, even fast connections were having a big delay especially in displaying PC's.  So I think frequently more than one person would &quot;see&quot; that they were first to a mob, when in fact they may not have been.  This was an especially big problem if you tried to pull a mob to another location.  Most people are going to see a mob, by itself, and see no PC near it, when a zone is so overfilled.<BR>
<BR>
Sure there was some intentional stealing going on, and that really stinks.  But I tend to assume that the majority of it was not.  I could, of course, be wrong and maybe it was all intentional, but its at least something to consider while making that &quot;Never help again&quot; list :)<BR>
<BR>
Legarak 26sk<BR>

