	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I am not on Tallon Zek, I am on Lanys T'vyl, but I experienced most of the same problems everyone has mentioned.<BR>
<BR>
I went to EK on my own at first and was surprised that so many things conned blue to me (19 Druid).  Why was I surprised?  Because when I checked the list of 125 players upon initially entering the zone, I was one of the lower level participants there.  The majority were easily 35 and up.  <BR>
<BR>
I did some fighting on my own but had a distinct problem finding things to fight.  Why, you ask?  Because while I was fighting a pawn, a reaver or a skeletal monk, boom, some high level caster would spell-cast it right out from under my nose.  Why would some lvl 50 wiz (as an example) need to do that to a 19 Druid?<BR>
<BR>
The next day, I returned with my tank partner (19 monk) and we put together a group that rocked!  All of us ranged from 18 to 21 and we had 6 different classes represented.  (Besides us, we had a warrior, a cleric, a chanter and a wiz.)  It was great because not only were we getting great experience, we also helped each other anytime we had a corpse with a loot item.  We would hold it for the person who had the right class.  Everyone was making out well and then we ran into two problems:<BR>
<BR>
1)  Solo high-levels were taking on too many wraiths and big monsters at once, then very rudely training them right past us.  We weren't even standing near the bridge!  This happened no matter where we stood.  Each of us died at least twice as a result.<BR>
<BR>
2)  We literally had several high-levels start camping whatever our tanks pulled!  Why?  Because nothing would agro on them since they were too high.  They once again had to spell-cast them away while our tanks were bringing them back to the group.<BR>
<BR>
Look, I could care less if a bunch of high-level folks decide that they want to loot the h*ll out of a lower level place.  Hey, I occasionally do it at Crushbone to make money.  Those are the perks of leveling up in the game.  However,  to have such high-level characters lower themselves to such petty tactics was unnecessary at best, pathetic at worst.  <BR>
<BR>
It would be unfortunate to have to establish rules to &quot;make&quot; people play fair, but if folks can't control themselves...<BR>
<BR>
Brigitmorgaine<BR>
Tunare's Servant<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
