				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I spent most of  my time over the weekend in EK and have an observation i would like to share.  <BR>
KS is simply unavoidable.  With 200 people in the zone it is impossible for most computers to show all the mobs and players that are on the screen.  I admit i even KS a few mobs because i was unable to see others attacking it. I know its a major annoyance &lt;hangs his head in shame&gt;, but i would always throw them a few heals and go find something else to beat on.  <BR>
I also beleive the idea that all drops are randomly on all mobs is a load of bull.  After easily spending 40+ hours in the zone, you can narrow objects drops to certian mobs.  <BR>
Also i send a plee to all players to not give in to greed.  Nothing annoys us players more then some rich guy comming in and shout &lt;will pay 1K for *insert the item you want here*&gt;.  I urge you all to shout them out and give a chance to all people after the item.<BR>
