	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I don't know how the event's were on your server, but let me describe the ones I witnessed on Tunare:<BR>
<BR>
1.  N. Ro -- Event starts: 1:00.  Event ends: 1:05.  Yes, someone has killed the High Priest (quest giver) again, despite everyone being asked repeatedly to leave him alone.  High level casters were running around killing mobs with a single spell.  KS'ing was rampant, and most people were anything from rude to obnoxious to downright hostile.<BR>
<BR>
2.  W. Commons -- werewolves in zone: maybe 30.  Players in zone: about 120.  Players in zone that could possibly get experience from the lvl 10-25 mobs - about 3.  You do the math.  WC was truly &quot;A Howling Nightmare&quot; -- flagrant ks'ing, cursing that would turn your hair white, flaming, spamming, and so on.  <BR>
<BR>
3.  E. Karana - zoned in with 120 players (heard that the zone actually crashed later on... glad I didn't stay long.)  Volumes of angry /shouts accusing KS'ers scrolled across my screen so fast I almost went LD.  After a particularly frustrating half-hour in W.C. I didn't even bother looking around.  Back into the gorge for me.<BR>
<BR>
4.  Rathe Mountains.  One of my characters (troll shaman) is high enough level to participate, but I didn't even bother.  That undead dragon they kept talking about didn't sound too friendly, and by this time, I'd had about enough with the events.  Can't really say what the mood was like there but I have a real good guess...<BR>
<BR>
I'm not coming down on the events.  They were a great idea... making things &quot;dynamic&quot; and different for a little while.  And I know a lot of people got some nice items.  Even lower levels got some good gear (yeah... whatever was picked over by all the high level bottom-feeders.)  And I'm not just griping because I'm bitter that I didn't get anything... in fact, I did manage to snag a nice bracelet for my mage, and a pretty good head piece for my shaman (a really nice enchantress held it for me after I set up a sow/regen station at the tunnel.)  =)<BR>
<BR>
But something really should be done differently next time to keep these events from consistently bringing out the worst in a few greedy people who don't care about ruining someone else's gaming.<BR>
<BR>
When someone complained about being ksed from a mob that they could have gotten exp from in W.C. he was told &quot;this is a loot event, go somewhere else for exp&quot;.  As if he didn't have a right to even be in the zone!!  More blunt, at a N. Ro event, someone had the nerve to shout &quot;if you're level 20 and under leave now.&quot;  Ridiculous!!  The event was MADE for pre-level 20 --  not a single mob in it was over about level 16 or so (except the high priest and the summoned snake.)  It would have been nice if the lowbies could have participated.<BR>
<BR>
So what should be done?  Here's my idea:<BR>
<BR>
1.  In my opinion, next time there should be events for all levels from 10-60 spread across a 10-12 zones on all continents instead of just four zones on Antonica.  That way, every one has an appropriate place to go.<BR>
<BR>
2.  Quest giving mobs (i.e. the High Priest in N. Ro.) should have 100% magic resistance and be unkillable.  They should death touch any one who so much as raises a rusty dagger to them.<BR>
<BR>
And I know I'm going to get flamed for this last one:<BR>
<BR>
3.  Each event mob needs to have trivial-looting enabled.  I know that's probably not possible with the way the zones are coded now, but it would be nice if it could be done for next Halloween.<BR>
<BR>
To be honest, When I first heard about &quot;trivial combat&quot; looting code, I thought it was ridiculous.  But this weekend has definitely changed my mind.  So you're a high level and want some &quot;phat lewt&quot; from a special event?  You should have to earn it... and not just by decapitating some level 10 mob with a single sword stroke either.  Of course you can always loot the corpses for what has already been picked over by the low levels if you wish.<BR>
<BR>
Just my thoughts on the matter, for what it's worth.  I was glad to see the special events this year -- I thought they were very well done.  But I have to say, I'm also very glad to see them end.  Now back to leveling my warrior (level 12... of *course* he didn't get any of the special items.)  :(<BR>
<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
